 Morgan which is definitely worth a read."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/33af7b8879cdcdfdb5edb7b1f265fd9c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":430,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/430/richard-smith-unna","reputation":7703,"display_name":"Richard Smith-Unna","accept_rate":90},"score":1,"post_id":2776,"edited":false,"creation_date":1340896301,"comment_id":3982,"body":"I&#39;m very interested in this too. David Attenborough once did a radio programme about the aquatic ape hypothesis, and you can <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/science/scarsofevolution.shtml\" rel=\"nofollow\">listen to it free online<\/a>."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b9ab37a714c62cfdc39c2c57601c2cee?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1067,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1067/c0zmic","reputation":162,"display_name":"c0zmic"},"score":0,"post_id":2776,"edited":false,"creation_date":1340896554,"comment_id":3983,"body":"Thanks for the link Richard"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/de2c4fd753821f85c74d886aa17410de?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":107,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/107/kmm","reputation":8486,"display_name":"kmm"},"score":3,"post_id":2776,"edited":false,"creation_date":1340995979,"comment_id":3996,"body":"In short: No. <a href=\"http://johnhawks.net/weblog/topics/pseudoscience/aquatic_ape_theory.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">johnhawks.net/weblog/topics/pseudoscience/&hellip;<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/895385d49eb1f04c5ee1f8d7734f3a62?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":997,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/997/noah-snyder","reputation":1332,"display_name":"Noah Snyder"},"score":0,"post_id":2776,"edited":false,"creation_date":1341019511,"comment_id":3997,"body":"See also: <a href=\"http://www.aquaticape.org/whyanthro.