er, there are one-eyed invertebrates, including <a href=\"http://biologicalexceptions.blogspot.com/2015/03/the-eyes-have-it.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">copepods<\/a>. (One copepod genus bears the scientific name <em>Cyclops<\/em>.) Answering your first question, copepods reportedly lack depth perception. There may be other one-eyed invertebrates, but I'm not an expert on inverts (there are too many species to count let alone study!).<\/p>\n","answer_id":42140,"question_id":42127,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1452302100}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/42127/are-there-animals-mammals-which-only-have-one-eye","last_activity_date":1452302100,"creation_date":1452265446,"answer_count":1,"title":"Are there animals / mammals which only have one eye?","body":"<p>Do all animals (of a certain size and not thinking about worms) have the possibility to perceive depth?<\/p>\n\n<p>Do all mammals have at least two eyes? Are there mammals with more than two eyes?<\/p>\n","question_id":42127,"tags":["zoology","vision","eyes","sensory-systems"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":42140,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":350,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kIqWF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19099,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19099/another-homo-sapien","reputation":1004,"display_name":"another 'Homo sapien'"},"closed_date":1451695427,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f524f51edb2e0e559de5f027217b2d47?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14815,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14815/ro-siv","reputation":535,"display_name":"Ro Siv","accept_rate":97},"score":0,"post_id":41926,"edited":false,"creation_date":1451654077,"comment_id":71381,"body":"Doesn&#39;t the bacteria flora in some higher vertebrates (ie: cows) allow for the celluase, and therefore the digestion of cellulose? We lack the bacteria and ther