st to let the sample dry out inside the tube (e.g. using a desscant), or store it at room temperature?<\/p>\n\n<p>Will it be possible to store it for e.g. a week before sending the batch in for analysis?<\/p>\n","question_id":42107,"tags":["hematology","mrna"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":31,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Ovli8y73Z14/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAdE/6kuQ2CyBvxo/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":17575,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/17575/mrinal-gautam","reputation":23,"display_name":"Mrinal Gautam"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"score":0,"post_id":42066,"edited":false,"creation_date":1452243681,"comment_id":72034,"body":"Mung germinates over night, doesn&#39;t it ? Think of sprouts.."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Ovli8y73Z14/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAdE/6kuQ2CyBvxo/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":17575,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/17575/mrinal-gautam","reputation":23,"display_name":"Mrinal Gautam"},"score":0,"post_id":42066,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"edited":false,"creation_date":1452331979,"comment_id":72143,"body":"It does. But that wouldn&#39;t be the correct way to answer. Right? I mean, It&#39;ll be pure hunch and no scientific reason."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"