ecific for each\n  residue and each ligand molecule from restraint library files, which\n  are subject to continuous empirical update.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>The value given in this book (Table 12-1) for peptide bond C-N is 1.336 Ã with variance 0.023 Ã.<\/p>\n","answer_id":41818,"question_id":41817,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1451929460}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/41817/resolution-of-x-ray-crystallography","last_activity_date":1451929460,"creation_date":1451245544,"answer_count":1,"title":"Resolution of X-ray crystallography","body":"<p>A structure determined by X-ray crystallography has a resolution of 1.5 Ã. When I look at the coordinates, I find every backbone C-N distance is 1.32 Ã.i.e. Accurately predicted. If resolution is not good why every C-N bond distance is accurately predicted?<\/p>\n","question_id":41817,"tags":["proteins","lab-techniques","protein-structure","xray-crystallography"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":41818,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":46,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/40ae400cb04bc03eb9d6573bf4c1d804?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":11605,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/11605/201044","reputation":279,"display_name":"201044","accept_rate":78},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/aedf04941d1a31e7e252c36f2cf95a46?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":20732,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/20732/the-nate","reputation":145,"display_name":"The Nate"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/40ae400cb04bc03eb9d6573bf4c1d804?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":11605,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/11605/201044","reputation":279,"display_name":"201044","accept_rate":78},"score":0,"post_id":41999,"edited":false,"creation_date"