 human races. So it seems to me that you are comparing a species (human) with genera (bovines) and families (dogs). --- +1 for drift!"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ee29c100b902da648c818e59ab370869?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6268,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6268/what","reputation":218,"display_name":"what","accept_rate":75},"score":0,"post_id":16387,"edited":false,"creation_date":1396876915,"comment_id":22108,"body":"Well, and acutally I accept this answer :-) Your explanation on genetic drift explains the differences \u2013 and I&#39;m not sure about the races and families anyway, so this is perfect for me. Thank you!"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":1,"post_id":16387,"edited":false,"creation_date":1396877306,"comment_id":22109,"body":"Also, it has been shown in several studies that sheeps are able to recognize faces."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":1,"post_id":16387,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ee29c100b902da648c818e59ab370869?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6268,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6268/what","reputation":218,"display_name":"what","accept_rate":75},"edited":false,"creation_date":1396886078,"comment_id":22112,"body":"@what the pictures are to illustrate the variation within a lineage of ancestry more so - I wasn&#39;t focussing on species (tired this morning after a heavily delayed flight!) but of course there are still differe